Introduction

Lee Min Ho, known under his stage name Lee Know, is a South Korean dancer, singer-songwriter, and composer under JYP Entertainment. He is best known as a member of the boy group Stray Kids. He is also a member of its unofficial subunit Danceracha.

Lee Know started his career as a dancer, competing with his crew “Cupcakes” and serving as a backup dancer for BTS during their “Wings Tour” in early 2017. Although he auditioned for JYP Entertainment in 2015 and didn’t receive an immediate response, he persisted with his dancing career.

In 2017, he was called back and joined JYPE on July 15, 2017. Only months after he joined the company, on October 11, 2017, he was picked to participate in JYPE's survival show at that time titled "Stray Kids", where he was eliminated in episode 4. He eventually came back upon Park Jin Young's decision influenced by the audience voting which favored a 9-member group, securing his debut with Stray Kids.

Lee Know debuted as a member of Stray Kids on March 25, 2018, with their mini album "I am NOT".

On February 27, 2024, Lee Know was appointed as the youngest Member of 'Bob Pierce Honor Club', after donating 100 million won to World Vision’s Global Food Crisis Response, aiding children in poverty-stricken regions affected by climate change, additionally, Lee Know also previously contributed to earthquake relief efforts in Turkey and Syria.
